gomodel:SYNGO_1479  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig3 shows STED microscopy of betaII spectrin in combination with Homer (postsynaptic marker), Bassoon (presynaptic marker) and phalloidin, staining filamentous actin (mainly in spines). BetaII spectrin shows a periodic striped pattern in the dendrite that extends into the neck of spines and spine head. Supplementary Fig 5 shows an extended gallery of these spine images. betaII spectrin labeling does not seem to overlap with the active zone/PSD contact area indicated by the Homer and Bassoon staining.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Cultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared from Wistar rats of mixed sex at postnatal day P0-P1...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1479" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

